 Port Alfred - An inquest docket has been opened for investigation in Port Alfred after a human left foot clad in a black 'Nike' takkie washed ashore and was discovered by a local resident on Tuesday afternoon. "The lower limb from the knee until the takkie did not have any flesh on it," described police spokesperson, Captain Mali Govender. "The limb has been taken by the Forensic Pathology Services where analysis will be conducted." She said currently, there are no outstanding missing persons reported in the area and at neighbouring police stations. "However, earlier this month a suspect, who attacked local police K9 dog, Ounooi,and fled towards the sea where he went missing," Capt Govender said. "A search was conducted with negative results." Meanwhile, Ounooi is making great progress and will soon join her handler on the beat! "This human limb was found close to area where the suspect went missing into the ocean," she said. "This will be probed further to establish whether this limb belonged to the suspect." An appeal is made to any person, who may be able to assist with the investigation to contact the crime stop number on 0860010111 or the Port Alfred SAPS on 046 6042001. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 